      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The issue here is that your solution has a time complexity of O(n^2) due to the nested loops. To optimize it, you can use the fact that the number of divisors of a number i is equal to (i-1)*2 + 1. Here's the optimized version:\n\n```python\ndef solve_problem(n):\n    return sum((i-1)*2 + 1 for i in range(1, n + 1))\n```\n\nThis version has a time complexity of O(n), which should be fast enough to pass the big test cases. The `sum` function and generator expression are used to calculate the sum of the counts in a single pass, eliminating the need for the nested loops.",
